definition.value: A beta-lactam that is azetidin-2-one substituted by an ethyl group at position 4.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of viridicatin resulting from the deprotonation of the 3-hydroxy group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group of O-methyl-L-tyrosine. The major species at pH 7.3.
A glutamic acid derivative that is glutamic acid in which the carboxy group at position 5 has been replaced by a methoxycarbonyl group.
